Key Match Events: Jazz Chisholm Jr. hit a grand slam for the second consecutive game in the 3rd inning, contributing to the Marlins' early lead.
The Marlins scored 16 runs, with multiple home runs, including another grand slam by Chisholm Jr. in the 7th inning.
Atlanta Braves' Marcell Ozuna hit a home run in the 8th inning, one of their few highlights in the game.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game was played at loanDepot park in Miami, Florida, with an attendance of 22,051 fans.
The Marlins completed a three-game sweep of the Braves, securing their position in the NL East race.
